This program has only been tested under Solaris and Linux.  But it should be
easy to port it to other 32 bit Unixes.

To build and install the binary just type something similar to

  cd /usr/local/src
  gtar zxvf ~/import/smvflatten-<VERSION>-src.tar.gz
  cd smvflatten
  ./configure
  make
  install -m 755 bin/smvflatten /usr/local/bin

or if you have the test cases

  cd /usr/local/src
  gtar zxvf ~/import/smvflatten-<VERSION>-src.tar.gz
  gtar zxvf ~/import/smvflatten-<VERSION>-tst.tar.gz
  cd smvflatten
  ./configure
  make
  ./test/run
  install -m 755 bin/smvflatten /usr/local/bin


Armin Biere, 18. April 2000
